      "message": "[Major] Line 176: Calling `accepted()` directly on focus loss manually emits the TextField `accepted` signal, which bypasses Qt Quick Controls\u0027 normal condition that `accepted` is emitted only for Return/Enter and only when the input is acceptable. If this field uses a validator, invalid text can now be committed on blur. Prefer extracting the existing accept logic into a helper that checks `acceptableInput` or the component\u0027s existing validation path before emitting the root-level accepted signal.\n```suggestion\n                onActiveFocusChanged: {\n                    if (!activeFocus \u0026\u0026 acceptableInput)\n                        accepted();\n                }\n```",
